Cell.Data: Identifies the specification of content and rules that apply to the transaction.
Identifies the BII profile or business process context in which the transaction appears.
The identity of the Receipt Advice set by the sender. It must be a unique identity. The Identity together with the Issue Date and Issue Time gives the version of the Receipt Advice.
The date when the despatch advice is issued. Format = "YYYY-MM-DD"
The time when the receipt advice is issued. Format = "HH:MM:SS+timezone".
A code signifying the status of the Receipt Advice. Default is Original (9)
A code signifying the type of the Receipt Advice - Response to the Advanced Despatch Advice (D) or Response to the received Shipment (S).
A textual note for the delivery as whole.
A reference to the original order
Used to provide a reference to the order on which the despatch is based.
A reference to the Advanced Despatch Advice.
The ID of the Advanced Despatch Advice. The unique identity of the Advanced Despatch Advice is made up by ID, IssueDate and IssueTime in combination.
The date the Advanced Despatch Advice was issued.
The time the Advanced Despatch Advice was issued.
The time when the Advanced Despatch Advice was issued. Format = "HH:MM:SS+timezone".

To be used when the Receipt Advice is a response to the received Advanced Despatch Advice. The status Code describes whether the Advanced Despatch Advice is accepted or if it is rejected due to errors, and the supplier should send a new.
Text to describe the reason for the rejection.
Reference to additional documents relevant for this Receipt advice. Can be used for additional BEAst information on header level.
The reference number of added document
The type of reference. Must me part of UNCL1001. At least one of Document Type Code and Document Type must be used.
The type of reference that cannot be specified by a code. At least one of Document Type Code and Document Type must be used.
Group to describe an attached document. An attachment can refer to an external document or be included with the document being exchanged.
The referenced document can here be inserted as a binary object.
The mime code of the attached document.
The file name of the attached document
A reference to an attached document that is external to the document(s) being exchanged.
The Uniform Resource Identifier (URI) that identifies the external object as an Internet resource.

The Consignee is the person or organization to which the products will be or has been shipped and who is taking possession. It also defines the sender of the Receipt Advice. The role is carried out by the customer or on behalf of the customer.
Identifies the consignee party's electronic address
The name of the Delivery Customer Party.
The main address line in a postal address usually the street name and number.
An additional address line in a postal address that can be used to give further details supplementing the main line. Common use are secondary house number in a complex or in a building.
The common name of the city where the postal address is. The name is written in full rather than as a code.
The identifier for an addressable group of properties according to the relevant national postal service, such as a ZIP code or Post Code.
For specifying a region, county, state, province etc. within a country by using text.
An additional address line in an address that can be used to give further details supplementing the main line.

The electronic mail of the contact.

Use the Shipment group only when the Receipt Advice is used as a response to a received shipment.
Identifies a shipment. Freight forwarder's reference number.
Information from Goods receiver to Supplier.
Use a dummy value since this element is mandatory.
To report the status of the received consignment.
Specifies the status condition of the consignment.
The reason for this status condition or position, expressed as a code.
The reason for this status condition or position, expressed as a text.
This party defines the company providing the transport service
The name of the carrier that handles the delivery of the dispatched shipment.
Identification about the driver of the vehicle that delivers the despatched shipment.
The type of document used for identifying the driver, expressed in text.
The Date the goods or service was delivered.
The time on which the supply of goods or services was made or completed according to the delivery term. Format = "hh:mm:ss+timezone"
The date, time or period the goods or service was requested to be delivered on.
The requested delivery date or the start of the requested delivery period.
The start time of the requested delivery period.
The last date of the requested period.
The ending time of the requested delivery period.
Special delivery terms that exceeds the inco terms.
Delivery terms location. The location to which the delivery terms refer. Used to qualify the delivery terms e.g. "Terms of delivery are FOB Rotterdam"
Used to specify how the goods is marked and if there are any damages. If this group is used, all Transport Handling Units in the Advanced Despatch Advice must be included, not just some.
The SSCC identification code of this Transport Handling Unit.
Type of Transport Handling Unit. Use UN/ECE Recommendation 21.
A textual description of the damage on this TransportHandlingUnit.
Pallet cover broken, see attached photo.
Status of the Transport Handling Unit.
To report if there are any claims related to this Transport Handling Unit. If omitted, default is that the THU is received ok and with no damage or claim related to it.
A code describing the status of the TransportHandlingUnit.
A line detailing a kind of item received.
A unique identity on this line, normally an increasing sequence number.
Text conveying information that is not contained explicitly in other structures.
The total quantity received, including any rejected parts.
The unit of measure that applies to the quantity.
The quantity received short; the difference between the quantity reported despatched and the quantity actually received.
The unit of measure that applies to the quantity.
A code signifying the action that the delivery party wishes the despatch party to take as the result of a shortage.
The quantity rejected due to damage, quality issues or any other cause.
The unit of measure that applies to the quantity.
The reason for a rejection, expressed as a code.
The reason for a rejection, expressed as text.
A code signifying the action that the delivery party wishes the despatch party to take as the result of a rejection.
The quantity over-supplied, i.e., the quantity over and above the quantity ordered.
The unit of measure that applies to the quantity.
A reference to the order line associated with this receipt line.
The Orderline this Responseline refers to.
Reference to the sellers orderline number.
The order can be referred to at header level or here. Doing it here at line level it is possible to refer to multiple order in one document.
Reference to the sellers order number.
A reference to a despatch line associated with this receipt line.
The identity of the Despatch Advice line number referred to.
Information to describe and identify the item.

The buyer's identity on the item.

The seller's identity on the item.
Identifying information for this item, assigned by the manufacturer.
A standardized item number. Only one StandardItemIdentification can be used per line.

The scheme identifier of the Item standard identifier.
With specific properties, e.g., Item 123 = Chair / Item 123 Ext 45 = brown chair.
